[1
Date: Mon, 17 May 1999 10:00:49 -0400
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Agence France Presse, 17 May 1999 (edited)

A new case of bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) has been detected in
the western French region of Vendee, the 10th this year and the 59th since
1990, the Agriculture Ministry said Monday.
It was the second case of BSE reported in the Vendee region. The entire
herd of 49 cattle was slaughtered.
--
Dorothy B. Preslar
Director, AHEAD/ILIAD Project
Federation of American Scientists
e-mail: dpreslar@fas.org

